{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, there has been a shift away from using standard architectures, with the majority of recognized works focusing on customized model editing and the introduction of novel architectures designed to address these specific issues.",
    "Nonetheless, the use of pretrained networks remains prominent, as these models provide a strong foundation that can be further enhanced for segmentation tasks.",
    "U-Net and its derivatives continue to be the preferred choice, especially for 3D segmentation tasks involving CT scans and other volumetric data.",
    "The architecture's encoderdecoder structure, which leverages convolutional layers for downsampling and upsampling layers for detailed reconstruction, is highly effective at capturing the fine-grained structures inherent in fossils, such as osteons in bone sections and microstructure in fossilized shells (Qin et al. 2022).",
    "Customizations, including attention mechanisms and multi-scale feature extraction modules like atrous spatial pyramid pooling (ASPP), have proven instrumental in overcoming performance bottlenecks, leading to improved multi-class segmentation of microfossil species."
  ]
}